---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="Process — Axiom Atelier">
  <section class="process">
    <h1>How a Piece Gets Made</h1>

    <p>
      Every piece starts the same way: I look at the material longer than I work it.
      Quarter-sawn white oak, Peruvian walnut — each board already has a grain, a grade, a
      set of flaws and strengths that dictate what it can become before I ever pick up a
      tool.
    </p>

    <p>
      From there, the process is slow by design. A votive tray takes about twenty minutes
      once the form is understood. A side table takes closer to four hours. A commissioned
      piece can take a full workday or more. None of that time is wasted — it's spent
      removing what doesn't belong.
    </p>

    <p>
      I work out of a shared studio space, splitting my time between Axiom Atelier and frame
      and crate work for a fellow artist. It keeps the shop honest — busy, lived-in, a place
      where things are actually made rather than just photographed.
    </p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .process {
    padding: 80px 0;
    max-width: 700px;
  }

  h1 {
    font-size: 2.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 50px;
  }

  p {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin-bottom: 30px;
    color: #2a2a2a;
  }
</style>